D.q[2851] = "Think you\'re brave, do you? Go to Pandala! You have a mission to accomplish...";
D.q[3692] = "This bridge is solid. You can cross it.";
D.q[1539] = "This brain is rotten... you might as well want to throw it out! You\'ve not been quick enough...";
D.q[2629] = "This engagement was not really serious anyway... with 5,000 Kamas we\'d have a deal.";
D.q[1645] = "This fair is a real success. People meet each other and play, children titter... I think I just heard a Gobball crack a joke. It\'s a magical place.";
D.q[3416] = "This dungeon is said to have been built before the very first stone of the great wall of the Castle of Amakna was even laid.\nIt\'s some sort of temple devoted to dark cult.\nThis place is infested with dangerous rats that can still be considered as harmless if you compare them to their master, Sphincter.";
D.q[3065] = "This is gonna be some meal! I just had an idea to end the evening perfectly... Okay, can you bring me an engagement ring?";
D.q[2499] = "This is a local specialty. There are a lot of them on Pandala island: the Pandneken, the Pandwiser, the Pandaburg... You\'ll get to know them soon... *Knowing wink.*";
D.q[2237] = "This is cake I buy for Oz. It\'s pity... He stuff the face with the bread.";
D.q[3597] = "This is right. I\'m showing all our employees the basis. There\'s a lot to be done in this farm. Tell me, what are you interested in?";
D.q[4142] = "This is perfect! I\'m going to heal the Coralators right now, that way I won\'t be tempted to drink the potion myself.";
D.q[2539] = "This is not a legend! The goddess said to Grandapan that when the Dofus are united be gathered, the chosen one will be blessed by the gods!";
D.q[2055] = "This metal is very unusual... I wonder if it could be due to Xelor magic! Who knows! I\'ve transmuted it, it\'s now a noble and pure metal. Go and see the blacksmith, tell him I sent you. He\'ll forge a blade so fine it will slice the very air into little pieces!!!";
D.q[4955] = "This new REALLY annoys me. Ah, if only Allister was here now and if I wasn\'t locked up in these chains...\nIn the meantime, the temple needs to be built. Your orders are to bring be 50 Irons, 10 Coals, 10 Crackler Stones and 20 Tin.";
D.q[2453] = "This one will stay in the trolley for a while now.";
D.q[1872] = "This piece of fabric leads me to... leads me to believe that a thief found my house, had a look, fell in love with the place and couldn\'t resist taking it away with him. Humm... weeell, maybe that\'s a bit far-fetched. There might have been two of them... perfect!";
D.q[3251] = "This room is protected. Only four of the most courageous Dragoss in this sanctuary have received the power to use this magic door. They have within an item, relic or artefact that enables them to open it without the Dragons having to take them in their room. If you find all four items, you too will be able to enter this famous room. But before that, you\'ll have to find all four Dragoss since they can only go through the door when they\'re all together. The power of these items ONLY works when they\'re together.";
D.q[172] = "This tavern has been here since I was a little girl. My father regularly brought me here and I ended up deciding to become a waitress. \nThe innkeeper that owns the place is a really nice guy and well known for his generosity. You can talk to him if you\'re looking for a job, he\'s often snowed under with work.";
D.q[955] = "This tower is located in the lower part of the city. Its library is a treasure trove for anyone interested in magic.";
D.q[4224] = "This village, located on top of this giant tree, is inhabited by the Zoth people. They\'re old tourists who came to discover the island and became crazy after drinking water from the putrid peat bog. \nWhen you know what\'s in it, you can easily understand that something\'s wrong with them... \nHowever, they do live in peace, they rule themselves. They wanted to set themselves free from the society in which they lived. As long as no one disturbs them, they\'re well-behaved and calm.";
D.q[4947] = "Those Brakmarians are cooking something, I\'ll see find out what it is .... Whatever the case, you\'ve earned some rest. Come and see me when you\'ve recovered from your trip.";
D.q[5155] = "Time flows quietly by, heros are born, grow old and die, their names too may live or die. So why are you wasting your time talking to me!";
D.q[1965] = "Times are hard, my friend, especially for people who try to be smart...";
D.q[1381] = "Tik bistik prif iik cinik givik yik is ti shirik wit yik mik pirciptivinissik piwirs. Briknik mik bick simitinknik ti iktik inik ikfik yik givik mik tik righik tinknik, yik wilik bik pirciptivik fir ink instik.";
D.q[2758] = "To become a Gokwa, you must defeat a disciple of your level in a fair fight... while I watch!\n\nDon\'t forget to wear your outfit!";
D.q[6586] = "To be honest, I\'d rather not talk about it, especially since Danathor the attendant has passed a law which means that anyone who is caught talking about black magic, obscure rights or any other sorcery associated with demons can be thrown in jail.";
D.q[607] = "To build a raft, I\'ll need at least 6 floats, 4 straps to attach them, 2 boards to make a flat surface, a beam, a trunk for a mast, a sail in GOOD condition and at least 10 pots of Glu to stick everything together.";
D.q[2332] = "To buy something from the marketplace, you first have to decide what kind of items and how many of them you want to buy.\nIf several identical items are on sale, you can only buy the cheapest one.";
D.q[3315] = "To charge Brakmarians with my cavalry, I need quick, strong Dragoturkeys!";
D.q[1193] = "To find his grave, you need to go to the place I\'ve just marked on your card. \nYou can\'t miss it, I put flowers on the grave not so long ago...";
D.q[2005] = "To get essence of Dizbi, you\'ll need a Dizbi flower...";
D.q[3214] = "You\'ll need a key to get in, and I\'m the only one who has one - and believe me, there\'s no way I\'m giving it to a tourist! You\'ll have to sort one out yourself. That said, a skilled Handyman should be able to make a key for you that\'ll let you enter the labyrinth, using resources from local creatures.\nBe careful though - there\'s a dreadful curse in the labyrinth. Everyone who enters loses their memory and forgets where they last saved their position, which makes Recall Potions useless. But don\'t worry, I\'ll guide you along during the trip, and if you get lost I\'ll be able to help you find the exit!";
D.q[361] = "To make a bunch of lollipops, I need 60 units of Blue Jelly, 30 units of Strawberry Jelly, 25 units of Mint Jelly, 1 unit of Blue Royal Jelly and 1 unit of Royal Strawberry Jelly . If you find everything for me, I\'ll give you a really cool surprise.";
D.q[1216] = "To join our Order, the very least you can do to show us your merit\'s to bring us 1 Chafer Bone.";
D.q[4111] = "To make ‘em keys I need... let\'s see: 1 Piece of the Shell of Aeroktor the Warrior, 1 Piece of the Shell of Terrakubiack the Warrior, 1 Piece of the Shell of Ignilicrobur the Warrior, 1 Piece of the Shell of Aquabralak the Warrior and last but not least 1 White Dreggon egg.";
D.q[170] = "To make bread, you need Flour, Water and sometimes Yeast. Generally, the best breads are composed of several flours, but they\'re also a lot more complicated to cook.";
D.q[2833] = "To quit our order, you must give the city a Guildalogem.";
D.q[2973] = "To prevent you from being misled in the future, just listen to me carefully. There\'s an easy way to recognize a Dofawa: their magic content is very low... To check it, just consult your inventory, slide the egg from your bag to one of your pockets designed for the Dofus. If the effects are nil or almost nil, the egg is a fake! By the way, a Dofus is a dragon egg. You wouldn\'t believe how powerful these eggs are!";
D.q[5836] = "To reach the highest rank in our Order you have to do a lot more than just cut throats. I have a few tasks for you that relate to all that\'s been going on lately. If you get on well, I will consider you for promotion";
D.q[580] = "To thaaaaank the advennnturer *hic* hhherrrre is my incongruoussss treasure *hic* this ppoott that made mme staaart *hic* my dead poet-painter careeeeer of *hic*";
D.q[2684] = "Treble Pint! I can sense a lover of fermented drink from a hundred feet! What would you like?";
D.q[3502] = "Troofle and Fattrool for a lot *shows his filthy fingers and toes* of Bwork beer!";
D.q[5971] = "Trkkk crunchhh craack...";
D.q[6445] = "Treat me with some respect or I\'ll whip you. Got it? And you can call me Ma\'am, get it!";
D.q[3794] = "True friendship is like a kneecap... You don\'t know what it\'s worth till it\'s gone.";
D.q[3954] = "Uba Tesse is sending you? Pass on my regards to him and give him this scroll too.";
D.q[3956] = "Uba sent you, huh? In that case, take this scroll.";
D.q[6447] = "Ughhh, you\'re disgusting! It would be cruel to the Gobball to let you near him, besides, I don\'t want something I\'m going to eat myself to go licking you from top to bottom. Go find me that Sram and make sure that you keep your personal issues to yourself in future. God, just picturing you with a Gobball is disgusting me.";
D.q[5816] = "Up you stroll with your hands in your pockets! Are you hiding something.";
D.q[2096] = "Unlike us, Feca, intelligence is not the strong point of these damned creatures. One Gobball is missing. Could you go and find it? I think it may be near the underpasses.";
D.q[1442] = "Veerry goood. I prreefeer aa frraank demmon whhoo assuumeezz deefeaat annd wwhoo haas ressspeect foorr annciennts thaaan theesse biirdbraainns wee haavee nowaadayys. Thhaat wwilll beee alll.";
D.q[3387] = "Ver\' good! Here! Take this key for the next job. Get goin\'!";
D.q[3383] = "Ver\' good! Here! Take this key for the next job. Get goin\'!";
D.q[3384] = "Ver\' good! Here! Take this key for the next job. Get goin\'!";
D.q[3382] = "Ver\' good! Here! Take this key for the next job. Get goin\'!";
D.q[203] = "Very impressive! That nail is definitely the oldest I\'ve ever seen, or smelled.\n(Lanfeust passionately sniffs the nail). Worn and foul-smelling. Perfect!\n\nVery well, you can enter if you\'re not afraid.";
D.q[2388] = "Very good, you\'re my apprentice now. To practice your job, you need a setting machine. I\'ve some cheap ones if you\'re interested. Equip it and you\'ll be able to use real jewellers tables. You\'ll quickly recognize them, there are always a few gems on there... just like in this room!";
D.q[2663] = "Very well! With this Kouartz we should be able to do a BETA (Bold Expedition in Time round Amakna).\nI\'m going to send you to the village of Amakna in 633, before all this mess started. As I only trust myself, you\'ll have to give me this letter... well... to the me of the past...\n\nAre you ready?";
D.q[2774] = "Very well... You can now train at the Dojo. You can come practice every day of the week except Saturday when the level passages are performed.";
D.q[5238] = "Very well. This should... destabilise the stabiliser! Hahaha!!!";
D.q[1633] = "Very well... You\'ve paid for your crime. A guard is now going to bring you back to the border.";
D.q[3354] = "Visit the surrounding area. It\'s not too big but you\'ll find wonders in there!";
D.q[2250] = "Voilà! Doesn\'t he look great like that? Ally Steria will only need the four thighs. I usually keep the rest.";
D.q[5037] = "WHAT! A TOFU CHARM??!!! HOW DARE YOU!!!";
D.q[968] = "Wait a second, each of these boxes weigh 500 pods... so I\'d advise that you offload a little before...";
D.q[5335] = "Waff, wafff. Me Ouginak. Waff.";
D.q[3439] = "Wanna play with me?";
D.q[4039] = "Wait, give me a minute and my masterpiece will be complete!";
D.q[3818] = "Wading through a dungeon with a sharp sword and a good book of spells is probably the most exciting thing an adventurers will ever experience!";
D.q[7468] = "If you use this power, all of your characteristics will be reset to zero. You\'ll lose any points that you gained from characteristic scrolls but you\'ll get back everything else.\nDo you really want to continue?";
D.q[5596] = "Was it you I sent to Bonta to find out what they\'re plotting over there?";
D.q[4705] = "It looks like the straps of my Gobball leather bag but I do not remember having damaged it. I suppose all Gobball leather bags look the same. If you want to make sure, ask Ture Inge for my bag, he confiscated it when I was arrested.";
D.q[4395] = "Was Rigal any help to you?";
D.q[5090] = "Was it Danathor who sold me out? The traitor! You won\'t get your hands on me that easily.";
D.q[710] = "Watch out! A demon has entered the city of Bonta! What is the militia doing?...Darn it, I\'m the militia.";
D.q[4918] = "Watch out, the god Sadida is prone to losing his temper at the moment. He doesn\'t like people picking flowers. Protectors ceaselessly watch over his precious plants.";
D.q[6215] = "We Xelors are the most powerful race in the World of Twelve. Noone can beat us, not even the Bworker whose butt hide I peeled off to make this cape.";
D.q[2490] = "Watwatwaaat? I look like a Frog? I\'ll put on my new boots and boot you all the way to Pandala! You won\'t like that, believe me... Pandala is on the other side of town, heeee! Didn\'t even know that, did you... ohhh people are so stupid, I know just the thing for your kind! Pathetic little so and so...!";
D.q[4266] = "We are plotting against Bonta again and I\'ll soon need your favours.";
D.q[4478] = "We can\'t let him help the Bontarians. You have to find the smith in the Porcos\' Territory and convince him to work for us... by any means necessary...";
D.q[3029] = "We beat Bonta again last time, all the courageous ones enlist in Brakmar!";
D.q[3293] = "We be here!\nRat Dungeon in Bonta, big dungeon full of rats very powerful.\nWe eat Bontarians at every meal.\nWe not able to make difference between Bontarian and not Bontarian.";
D.q[1816] = "We found Heltan, unfortunately, he grew very old. He asked us all to bring him mud to have mud baths. And as he would say so well \'You cannot solely rely on the charity of the Xelors, you should ask a bucket of mud from the Mushd before each fight against a Dopple.\'...";
D.q[290] = "We don\'t have anything here. No neighbours, no running water, no entertainment, not even a local bloody supermarket!\nI had nothing to eat for 9 years, 11 months and 26 days. Believe me, sucking stones all day long is rather dull... I\'ve been dreaming of Rib Chops for nine years... oh forget it! If you bring me some Rib Chops, I\'ll give you sesame seeds.";
D.q[4732] = "We have most of the materials, but we need a special hammer to forge a demonic blade - we need the Hammer Hitocracy. And to get one of those, we need to exorcise a Hammer of Light of the good spirit that animates it.";
D.q[2653] = "We\'ve been to the most famous schools of combat in the world - Ecaflip\'s playful claw, Sadidas\' natural magic powers... We are now experienced enough to face them, but when it comes to a new opponent with new tricks, we\'re at a bit of a loss. Our school is aiming at evolving so that soon enough, our art will be capable of taking on all existing fight moves and will become famous throughout the world.";
D.q[6089] = "We hurried the creation of Bonta. We really should have taken our time and done things properly.";
D.q[6051] = "We musn\'t let our guard down. If we do, the Brakmarians will have the chance to spread their underhanded ways around the World of Twelve.";
D.q[6091] = "We must avoid open war between the cities, but unfortunately, not many people share my views.";
D.q[814] = "We took a real beating today and the men are tired and injured.\nHmmm. You might be of some use after all...\nGo to an Alchemist and bring me back some Pahoa Raid potions, or these 3 men here won\'t make it through the night.";
D.q[2109] = "We\'ll soon see if those apprentices are worthy... for this I need a lot of Gobball saliva. Could you bring me back about ten units?";
D.q[4490] = "We\'re thinking about the next plan. You are free to leave until we\'ve made up our minds.";
D.q[6351] = "We\'re stopping here because Rin\'gin and Billie Tell are still arguing about the colour of Amayiro\'s white hair.";
D.q[2272] = "Weeeeelll... So, you want to know more about the creatures lurking around here, right? It\'s quite simple... the further north or south you go, the more dangerous the creatures are, and the greater the chances are that you\'ll die. In the surroundings, and up to Amakna, there\'s nothing fierce... although some shady areas around Astrub haven\'t been quite so safe of late...";
D.q[1049] = "Weeaahhh... hazno beer no moorrre... hazno moniiii tooo... but zztill thirstyyyyy!";
D.q[7081] = "We\'ve been opening the doors of our temple to representatives of the other divinities for some time now.";
D.q[2843] = "Welcome to the Bonnawa chocolate Factory! You won\'t find better chocolate anywhere else. For that matter, you probably won\'t find any chocolate anywhere else!\nDon\'t hesitate to treat yourself and buy some products in my shop, as the slogan says What\'s good on your tongue is good in your soul!";
D.q[6444] = "Welcome to Bagrutte\'s Inn. I\'m the one who gives the orders to the customers, you got it.";
D.q[1680] = "Welcome to the Arena of the Gladiatrool! Sorry but this attractionation is momentaneously closeted, but come back soon if you want to see the ginormousest monster fighttles of all time!";
D.q[1685] = "Welcome to the Arena of the Gladiatrool! Come to test your endamina in a series of fighttles against scariffying monsters!\nWe don\'t accept Kamas here so you\'ll need 100 Trool Tokens from the Trool Fair!\n\nThe regules are quite simple: you just need to survive and to go as far as possible. After each figttle you have the popportunity to stop or to continue.\nPay attention, to make things a bit more hifficult, your powers will be belowered before each fighttle...";
D.q[932] = "Welcome to the Feubuk Inn, how can I be of service to you, young stranger?";
D.q[1276] = "Welcome to the Kikim Inn, what can I do for you, #1?\nSorry about last time, my mind sometimes goes blank...";
D.q[2844] = "Welcome to the Drunken Pandawa Inn, how can I help you?";
D.q[1903] = "Welcome to the Croa bakery, all our breads are baked according to the traditions of old. You\'ll understand what I\'m talking about instant your teeth pierce the crusty crustiness of my crusty crusts.";
D.q[4565] = "Welcome to the temple. Make the most of your stay by finding out about our ways and customs, and why not battle one of our dopples while you\'re here.";
D.q[1013] = "Well done #1. That boar from the plains should leave us in peace for a while.";
D.q[2267] = "Well as I told you before, I don\'t have any Hurrywood. But just look at this beautiful Elm wood, look at this masterpiece. What the hell do you want that Hurrywood for!";
D.q[3041] = "Well done adventurer! You seem foolhardy and I can tell that fighting doesn\'t scare you. You\'ll see wanted posters all around the jail. If you want to earn Kamas, there are a few outlaws to find throughout the entire World. Have a safe trip and may you live long! Before leaving, don\'t forget to read the book I\'ve just given you!";
D.q[1045] = "Well done! Though a bit too long. But you\'re better than a mass of rotting calcium. I appoint you to the rank of flunkey. Believe me, it\'s a great privilege.\nPlus, I even have a first job to entrust you with...";
D.q[3872] = "Well done! You proved your loyalty towards the King. But honestly ...I find it strange that the Rogues did not choose a better hiding place than that, given all that\'s been happening... That said, not everyone is fortunate enough to get in!";
D.q[2458] = "Well done! You\'ve understood how to use your compass. Now you should know that you can sit down anytime if you need to recover from your wounds after a fight.";
D.q[3793] = "Well done. You\'ll quickly learn how to take a character off this list... or how to make a list of people you don\'t like so much.";
D.q[3605] = "Well done. You\'re a good worker. Here is your wage.";
D.q[6112] = "Well soldier, have you come to report on the Assembly of Protectors?";
D.q[5726] = "Well to be honest, I don\'t know much about this statuette business. You should take a trip to Djaul\'s tavern to find out more. You often see the Brakmarians officers recovering from their injuries there...";
D.q[3908] = "Well looky here, a visitor... You must be shrewd to have found this hideaway... Here, take this!";
D.q[3823] = "Well look here, a puny little adventurer. I bet you couldn\'t even imagine what\'s waiting for you in this cave. Am I right?";
D.q[1117] = "Well what do you want? You\'re not too thrilled? I can defeat you whenever you like! Wait a second, I\'ll find my pals and we\'ll split you in two... You\'re lucky because my 50 pals aren\'t around otherwise you could have been in trouble. Alright, I\'m going!";
D.q[5509] = "Well what have we got here, a Bontarian, is it? What am I supposed to do now? Oh well, it\'s not my job, the underlings can do it... I\'m a bloody captain.";
D.q[3259] = "Well, I hope you\'ve got good earmuffs!\nHum.... By the way....\nJust to know, you\'re not a kid dressed up as an adult are you? \nYour parents really allowed you to come? \nBecause the last kid I took with me never came back...\nI bet he didn\'t want to leave my island but his mum\'s been chasing me all over the place since...\n\n*Looks over his shoulder*\n\nRight... Hurry up! I\'m off!";
D.q[3332] = "Well, I\'ll make it short for you. I need pieces of Kaliptus and Koalaks. ";
D.q[388] = "Well, I need 75 Arachnee legs, 60 Five-leaf clovers and 40 Karne Rider nails.";
D.q[1463] = "Well, are you coming?";
D.q[7621] = "By \'eck, there\'s a reet luverrleh spring flower, and no mistake! What\'re yer wantin, any road? Want to get in\'t windmill, do yer? Reckon I wouldn\'t be reet \'appy \'bout that, let me tell yer!";
D.q[209] = "Well, at least you seem cocky enough to fight the Boowolf. You can pass.";
D.q[1451] = "Well, at least if you die tonight, it won\'t be from the cold, ahahah!";
D.q[3593] = "Well, go and see my foreman. He\'ll explain to you what you need to do.";
D.q[3441] = "Well, if two children did come by this way, I haven\'t seen them!";
D.q[1033] = "Well, interested in expensive wares, hmm? Well... show me the money.";
D.q[4042] = "Well, it will be an honour to serve a prince.";
D.q[3181] = "Well, it seems Lord Crow appreciated your visit. He\'s been quite bored lately, as he\'s read all of the books in this library. Having the opportunity to play with you took his mind off things for a while. By way of thanks, he\'s asked me to give you one of his companions to take with you as a pet.";
D.q[4825] = "Amayiro told me how you dealt with the inquest. I trust you to prove me innocent.";
D.q[7023] = "So you\'re looking for the Tears of the Goddess? Do you know at least how they got there? Of course not.\nTo access the divine pantheon, Sacrier had to pass a test imposed by Ruhsu, the Lord of Demons. Taking Xelor\'s Clock in her hands, she felt the pain of the world and could not restrain her tears, which fell on the Clock and infiltrated into the workings of time itself. Upsetting the ages, the tears brought about the resurgence of the cities of Bonta and Brakmar, which were no more than dust long ago, and so the goddess Sacrier gave them a second chance.\nOne of her tears fell to earth in an arid and corrupt area south-west of Brakmar, and it is claimed that life and nature are struggling to take hold there. I\'ll show you where this place is supposed to be.";
D.q[4720] = "Of course, I often have a chat with him when he finishes his shift. He\'s always so friendly, always telling stories.";
D.q[1144] = "Well, once again, I\'m not in the least bit grateful. Although this will help us in the next few fight against those Bontarian swine.";
D.q[342] = "Well, take this potion for curing myxomawosis and don\'t come back. I only give one per person and its effects last for life.";
D.q[5684] = "Fine, I\'ll prepare the potion. But afterwards, bugger off and leave me alone, okay?\n...\nOh, that\'s really unfortunate, I have no more enchanted water. You will have to complete the potion yourself. You must go into the tunnels of the Enchanted Lakes area to find the underground river that feeds the lakes. Take a little water from the river and mix it with the potion. The magic will be activated and all that\'s left will be for you to make the person having a memory lapse drink the contents of the potion.\nRemember to take climbing ropes and a few other people with you, you never know...";
D.q[4295] = "Well, such a long list won\'t be easy to get. Let\'s start getting this stuff...";
D.q[6932] = "Hello, isn\'t this place beautiful? I\'ve spent a long time since I left the tumultuous life of an adventurer behind.";
D.q[834] = "Well, thanks to you I\'m back on my feet again! Heheh! Let\'s make hay while the sun shines, I\'ve a sudden craving for wealth. Do you feel like visiting the great jeweller, Mrs Azra Lazarus? I\'ve heard that she\'s wearing a priceless green diamond round her neck, it\'s called the \'Lung of the Plains\'... Bring it to me, by hook or by crook...!";
D.q[6991] = "Hello, I need your services again.\nI would like that Solar, the late Protector of the month of Javian, help Jiva in her struggle against Djaul. I have discussed this matter with Kosuke Ichazum and Larry Poller, who have confirmed it would be possible to permeate the Dawn Shard with the thoughts of this lost Iop.\nHowever, we have a problem. I do not know where and how to get such a thought, and Elviana Tirips, Master of the Order of the Salvatory Spirit, doesn\'t know either.\nAs alchemists are able to create Remembrance Potions, I thought they might be able to help us. Alas, Larry Poller wasn\'t able to. However, due to his advanced age, it might be that Merlinmagus Ambrosius could tell us something.\nGo see him and ask him.";
D.q[4799] = "Bonta is a beautiful city, it\'s a pity that its sewers are so dirty and disgusting. Hey! Come to think of it, they remind me of you a little.";
D.q[5738] = "Bravo, I expected no less from you. Take these few Kamas as a reward for your valour.\n...\nI miss my little piwis. I still remember the time when the city of Bonta had its resurgence. We lacked for young recruits so badly, I put piwis through military training so as not to lose the upper hand. Although those days are long gone, I have decided to train a small commando unit of elite piwis. For this I\'ll need some sesanabolic seeds, and only Merlinmagus Ambrosius knows their secret. Go ask him about them.";
D.q[2692] = "Well, well, well... Look who\'s here?! A disciple of the goddess Pandawa... Welcome! It\'s for an initiation? Sorry, no time!";
D.q[2674] = "Well, well, well... So you weren\'t born yesterday, were you? Welcome in the World of Twelve! Open your eyes wide: You\'re just born on our ancestral island. Right in front of you, you can see the statue of our beloved goddess.";
D.q[4707] = "Amayiro sent you?\nWell, a few days ago, a stranger asked me to meet them in the Atyu Servis Inn. I asked him why but he never answered and got lost in the crowd. Curious, I went to the inn.\nArriving there, I introduced myself to the innkeeper and it was at this point that someone entered the inn shouting and accusing me of treason. The militiamen came and took me, and searching my bag they found a confidential Bontarian document I was supposedly about to sell to Brakmar.\nI swear by Silvosse that I have nothing to do with this matter. I had never seen the document before.";
D.q[2372] = "Well, well... Here comes Grossewer Rat Terror! All the Astrub rats know you now! What do you want?";
D.q[4911] = "Did Ebru Of El send you? I have to be honest and tell you that my research was fruitless. I have, on the other hand, heard of a medium capable of entering into contact with souls. She disappeared without trace a decade ago and her family remained discreet about the circumstances of this sudden disappearance. However, Xeloro Verpowered knew her well enough and might be able to tell you something. If she\'s in town, she\'ll be south of the arena. She often gets advice about fairyworks from Moob Tsinhcetoryp.";
D.q[4888] = "Well, yes. Alright, I\'m going to let you fight and I\'ll make out as if you lose.";
D.q[7030] = "My grandfather invented the mask so that he could visit the Sidimote Moor caves. Experienced tailors can make you one if you bring them the necessary materials. I\'ll make you a list, it will be easier.\nWhen you have your mask, you\'ll be able to walk under Brakmar safely as well.";
D.q[6835] = "That place is still open? I don\'t understand, I told Danathor to take steps to close it down. I authorise you to go but in the utmost discretion, I do not want people to misunderstand the presence of a loyal militiaman there.";
D.q[2367] = "Well, you know, Dofus and all that stuff... You know, dragon eggs that give powers, you can\'t find a lot of that around, and with all those adventurers arriving, it\'s the egg rush! Well, I gotta go, have a good trip! And may the stones be soft under your feet!";
D.q[5685] = "Ah, that\'s some good drinking right there! Sure, I remember the statuettes. My wonderful little sister stashed one in the Tofu House. Wasn\'t that a great idea? Sumens made the statuette look like something else, too, so you\'ll need to look hard for it in case you miss it. Was that everything your master wanted to know? In that case, you can say hello to him from me and say that Bonta isn\'t bad, for a one-horse town.";
D.q[4256] = "Well, your cursed sword seems to be completely useless. It\'s sharpened but the blade isn\'t well-balanced and I\'m sure that you have to make two attempts before you can hit your target! If you want, I can fix this.";
D.q[2847] = "Well. Let\'s continue. What is the fifth level of Pandawushu called?";
D.q[5081] = "Well. What do we have here? I am sensing a powerful evil aura around you. Do you want me to eat you right away, or would you rather have a chat first?";
D.q[3019] = "Well... if you\'d rather die as an idiot and haunt a crappy grave for ever... Your call...";
D.q[7622] = "By \'eck, so yer think yer summat special with yer two little lumps, do yer? Well, \'appen as we\'re reet kindly folk where I\'m from, I\'ll let yer in this time.";
D.q[6997] = "And then? Just as Otomai was about to give me the award, I realised that real power does not come from the Dofus. You\'re probably wondering what I mean by that, so let me explain.\nCollecting the necessary souls would have taken years. I was prepared to do it, but I hadn\'t expected what would happen next. As I started to capture the first souls with my friend Meuh Sieurchance, I met other adventurers hired by Otomai. These people spontaneously gave me the souls they had caught themselves without asking for anything in return. Among them were two other famous soul hunters, Dame Sdrop and Layke, and their help was greatly appreciated.";
D.q[3220] = "Well... What do you want? Are you already lost? You want your mooommy!";
D.q[2099] = "Well... That\'s not a very good start! *she starts screaming* Daddy, Daddy!";
D.q[3021] = "Well... if you come back to visit me, it will be because you\'ll have found the sign we talked about.";
D.q[5725] = "Strange, very strange. This is the first time I\'ve been told such a story, excepting the stories of Captain Igloute. Do not tell anyone else. I will immediately tell Justfa so that he can quarantine the area.\nIn fact, Dike Tarak was not captured by these creatures, but he fled and lost his way. He just returned safely to Bonta.\nBut back to your promotion. If you want to become Supreme Assassin, you\'ll have to make your way to Brakmar and ask our spy about Statuette of Sumens that the Brakmarians just recovered.";
D.q[3957] = "Well...Let\'s try something else... Find an Obese Tofu\'s nest and bring me an egg. Hurry!";
D.q[2316] = "Wellllllll! Well done! I think we\'ve come to an agreement! So, we were saying... *rubbing his hands*";
D.q[4685] = "Well? Hurry up and go see Domen, I need you for my blade.";
D.q[6821] = "Hmm... good evening. Do you know that Danathor intends to pass a law legalising Tofu fighting?\nObviously not. Go and bother someone else, I\'ve got a card game to win.";
D.q[3059] = "What a fantastic heap of rocks! Thank you. But my builders are hungry. If you could bring me back some wheat, I could feed these strapping gentlemen.";
D.q[2595] = "Your path has been long, disciple, but at least you\'re on the right one, the one leading to the evil forest... But before you even think of going there, you should go talk to our Dopple tamer. Try and improve your fighting techniques on those creatures! You\'ll be glad of the practice once you reach your destination. Some say this forest has been forgotten by the gods... If you can\'t beat a dopple, I forbid you to set foot on this cursed land... It would be plain suicide!";
D.q[1499] = "What a clumsy fool you are! If you don\'t know where to go, ask someone who does. The librarian of Amakna knows everything, he might know about your case. JUST GO now!";
D.q[6792] = "He was little, uh no, he was taller than Kit Dingaround. He was dressed in red... yes, red, that\'s right. He spoke with a strong accent and smelled of something that stings, what\'s it\'s called now? Ah yes, sulphur. He smelled of sulphur.\nHis race? uh... not Sram, that\'s for sure. I would say an... let\'s see... an Ecaflip? Yes, a Ecaflip dressed in grey who smelled of sulphur, uh, dressed in red, I mean. I can write a description on paper if you want.";
D.q[5723] = "It was dark and everyone was asleep except the lookout when a flare bloomed over our heads. We saw small, dark shapes by its light and when it disappeared, Dike Tarak was gone. The whole thing did not last more than ten seconds. The children were immediately escorted to Bonta while a handful of us went in search of Dike Tarak, but without success.\nI\'ll indicate on your map exactly where we were.";
D.q[6949] = "I\'ve heard much good about you from Ebru Of El, it seems that once again you surpassed yourself.\nYour success has also reached the ears of Quartermaster Danathor, and he\'s asked to see you urgently. He needs your help to prepare a magical gift, or something like that.";
D.q[1210] = "What are you doing here, slave of Goodness?\nBe careful Chaos doesn\'t destroy you!";
D.q[6433] = "What are you doing here? Get out of here and forget everything you\'ve just seen, or I\'ll cut your throat. Got it?";
D.q[6904] = "I don\'t like this court, I don\'t like the militia either. In fact, I don\'t like anyone here. This place gives me hives, I have to get out of here as soon as possible.";
D.q[5737] = "I expected better from you but I had prepared myself for this eventuality. The statuette that that Brakmarians stole is a fake. The real Statuette is right now hidden away in a safe place under the protection of Jiva.\n...\nI miss my little piwis. I still remember the time when the city of Bonta had its resurgence. We lacked for young recruits so badly, I put piwis through military training so as not to lose the upper hand. Although those days are long gone, I have decided to train a small commando unit of elite piwis. For this I\'ll need some sesanabolic seeds, and only Merlinmagus Ambrosius knows their secret. Go ask him about them.";
D.q[4915] = "I thought as much... I don\'t like competition, so you\'d better clear off before I give you a well placed smack with a shovel.";
D.q[5980] = "What are you doing there? You\'re not a Wabbit you know.";
D.q[6975] = "I didn\'t think you\'d get on so well with us so quickly. This fragment of time must be really important if you are willing to violate your principles so readily. I already managed to get one in advance, here it is.\nIf you still need the services of the Rogues, we will gladly help you, if the pay is good...\nNow, go back to Danathor, I\'m tired of seeing your Bontarian mug in my hideout.";
D.q[6718] = "What are you doing there? You\'re not allowed past, and even if you do go by, you\'ll get lost down there without a guide. I\'m not allowed leave here and I\'m getting a bit peckish, so how about you go get me some Intre Bread. In return, I\'ll be your guide! Let me warn you though that there are some dirty beasts down there and I can\'t guarantee you\'ll come out alive, especially if you go alone.";
D.q[3574] = "What are you standing around for? You want some work? Well, get going and rid us of these terrible creatures... quick, I don\'t have time for lazy cowards!";
D.q[5519] = "What can I do for you, Bontarian?";
D.q[6948] = "I think that the vision refers to the path taken by your Spirit of Light. It seemed filled with sadness and its tortured soul was guided to the Cemetery of Brakmar. I do not know the link with the second part of the vision yet, but you will probably find it in due course.\nI think I\'ll stay here a little longer. Even if I was locked up by force, I found calm and serenity here. I am no longer plagued by a multitude of visions of all kinds and I can concentrate on the few visions I have. Feel free to come back and see me again.";
D.q[4322] = "What are you waiting for? Every second counts! Go to Milone\'s house!";
D.q[5520] = "What can I do for you, Bontarian?";
D.q[1421] = "What can I do for you, Bontarian ?";
D.q[4859] = "I am saddened that you took sides against Kit. I really can\'t understand why you would do such a thing and I hope something else will come up to prove his innocence.";
D.q[7039] = "What characteristic should this scroll modify?";
D.q[7041] = "What characteristic should this scroll modify?";
D.q[5083] = "What did you find over there?";
D.q[1041] = "What dexterity! Well done... As you wanted it, Musa the Wolf Killer bestows the name of hunter upon you.";
D.q[4924] = "I\'ll show you that when it comes to making dolls, Sadidas are even better than their reputation suggests.\nWe assemble the leather like so, put the eyes here...\n.......\n.....................\nAnd there you have it, a beautiful Feca doll.\nNo need to thank me, it was a pleasure to make it. You can take it to your spirit now, I\'m sure she\'ll be really pleased with it.";
D.q[2060] = "What do you mean you don\'t have a sword? Come back to me when you\'re armed, kid!";
D.q[6971] = "Nice work, my Rogues couldn\'t have done better. So how does it feel to have robbed your own city? Hahaha.\nI found out more about the situation and I heard that the Demons of Hours exchange stolen Fragments of Time for the souls of Xelor Dopples, specifically those called \"Nebgib\". They need 24 in total, do not ask me why.\nYou probably do not know how to get in contact with the Demons of the Hours, so I can do it for you. Come see me with the soul stones, I\'ll take care of the rest.";
D.q[6929] = "The Xelor tile is located in Feudala Village, but I do not know where exactly. I have not set foot there since then and at the time I didn\'t know the places I do now. Only a disciple of Xelor can use its magic, provided they have equipped a Xelor\'s Past and are in possession of a Temporal Powder.\nIf you want to know where the Enutrof tile is, go and talk to Nystig. He moved with his wife to the south of Dragoturkey Territory because he took up hunting and cooking Dragoturkeys.";
D.q[3993] = "What do you want from me? That I serve a Wabbit? But they\'re weak, don\'t know how to handle weapons and speak stwangely.";
D.q[6733] = "What do you want now? Have you not finished harassing me yet?";
D.q[4786] = "The militia? Who do you take me for? I had no evidence and they would have dragged me off for defamation, the clowns! What do you think? They look after themselves.";
D.q[678] = "What do you want now?";
D.q[1118] = "What do you want sonny, I\'ve all anyone could wish for here: money, money and money! You can buy whatever you feel like. Power, friends... everything! But just don\'t try stealing from me. If I so much as suspect that the thought has crossed your mind, I\'ll poke your eyes out with your own thumbs.";
D.q[5098] = "What do you want this time?";
D.q[6390] = "What do you want to know?";
D.q[2753] = "What do you want to know young disciple #1?";
D.q[6883] = "Hypnomeows are a rare species of Bow Meow. They are malignant and devious creatures, and are so lazy they resort to hypnotising innocent victims to fulfil their every whim.\nThe victims see the Hypnomeow as an adorable little frail and sickly creature, in need of protection and constant care. It\'s like a kind of Eniripsa transformation, in appearance at least.";
D.q[6568] = "What grace, you impress me! For now I want you to go soothe the Boowolf into submission using the moves you just showed me. And don\'t forget to bark a bit, or he\'ll realise it\'s a trick.";
D.q[6035] = "What have you got? Do you want my photo?";
D.q[5587] = "What is that smell? Some kind of Koalak urine potion? Lice shampoo?";
D.q[6810] = "Thank you, I didn\'t think that the militia would take my security seriously, it must be really important if you\'ve gone to so much trouble.\nIn reality Kit Dingaround came by but he just talked to the Shoemaker Merchant. He then went to Atyu Sirvis\' Inn. I didn\'t see anything out of the ordinary.\nHowever, the night after his arrest a masked man in grey who reeked of rotten Snapper and rubbish came to see me. He told me what I had to answer were I asked about Kit Dingaround, but he also threatened to kill my boars then kill me afterwards if I refused to cooperate. That\'s why I lied, sorry.\nThe masked man then accosted that pretty girl Clara Daul when she was returning to her house but she gave him an enormous slap across the cheek. Ah, if only I had her courage...";
D.q[7009] = "Thanks, I\'ll use it on Meuh Sieurchance. If he gets his memory back, you can meet him at his home in the breeder village. Otherwise, it will mean he\'s got lost on the way.";
D.q[1980] = "What should I do? My friend is seriously ill. But I can\'t leave her here alone long enough to look for a remedy. What should I do?";
D.q[5691] = "Wonderful! I\'ll put it away somewhere safe. Make the most of your free time by finding out about the benefits that your new rank, Mistress of Scrolls, brings you.";
D.q[6950] = "My experts are still unable to decipher the Cave-dwelling Bwork Magus\' grimoire, I was counting on its secrets to crush Brakmar once and for all. I cannot admit this setback to Jiva, so I decided to make her an offering of invaluable and incredible power that might help her in her struggle against the treacherous Djaul.\nYou understand now why I cannot entrust this task to just anyone. As you serve our city faithfully and the Masters of Orders have great respect for you, I have decided to confide this mission of utmost importance to you.";
D.q[3444] = "Do you want something to eat?";
D.q[6793] = "Hmm... I agree with you, Robin Gaywould is hiding something from us. Look at his writing, it\'s all over the place. There, you see the words he uses? He\'s hesitating, that\'s for sure. This message was written in the grip of fear, it seems that Gaywould is afraid of something.\nYou\'d better go back and ask him what it is.";
D.q[2196] = "What the...?! I\'ve just watched you die... You must have some time left, then. My vision is muddy of late... it must be all that wood? I told you to bring virgin stuff! Ah, that bloody Oli Venders! Well, I suppose I\'ll need a blue larva skin to clarify my vision. Here! Take this hammer and go get one!";
D.q[6787] = "What the... aaatchoooo!";
D.q[3033] = "What will the subject of my next book be? You, maybe?";
D.q[6924] = "Nosilla has been imprisoned for several years in a cave whose opening is blocked by a magical mechanism. Three slabs keep the entrance closed, and I know how to disable one.\nThis slab is located on Minotoror Island. Only Ecaflips can disable its magic, they must equip an Ecaflip\'s Luck and have a Piece of the Crackpot Treasure in their inventory. Unfortunately, the three slabs must be deactivated simultaneously to unlock access to the cave.\nI can not help you more, if not only to give you the identity of the Xelor. Her name is Kwartzwatch, she is the Xelor responsible for greeting those souls that have just arrived from Incarnam.";
D.q[6823] = "Ask the other customers, they\'ll know better than me.";
D.q[5016] = "What!? *Hick* did Danathor put a good word in for me with the young ladies? That\'s luck for you.\nThank him on my part *hick*.";
D.q[2498] = "What\'s the McSheth?";
D.q[6953] = "Why a wild boar? To do immoral thingssssshhh with it, of courssssshhe!\nAhahah! No, it\'sssshhhh not what you sssshhhhink, it\'sssshhhh for a barbecue... becaussssshhhhe Plain Boar meat goessssshhhh really well with Rib Chopsssshhh.";
D.q[4229] = "What you see before you took all of our experience with the elements to create. We now know how to make ice, and to maintain microclimates which allow us to manipulate the evolution of the Otomai bacteria. For better... and for worse.";
D.q[4120] = "What colour is William Lowson\'s white Dragoturkey?";
D.q[3747] = "What\'s the matter? You\'re having trouble crafting? Do you need some help?";
D.q[5733] = "As you are offering to relieve the guard, no problem at all.\nDon\'t you know what I\'m talking about? I\'m talking about guarding the Statuette of Sumens that\'s stored in the basement of our Tower. Our spies have informed me that the Brakmarians want to steal it, so I want someone trustworthy and strong enough to protect it. Do not hesitate to call in reinforcements if you fear you are being overwhelmed, though.";
D.q[6339] = "What, what does it mean when... I see, you think you\'re smart don\'t you? Take this newly trained Whitish Fang and we\'ll see if Roy Sigfred\'s method is as effective as he says it is. I\'ll show you where the ambush happened. Hurry up and report back to me when you\'re done.";
D.q[4115] = "What\'s your favourite colour?";
D.q[4289] = "What? Betray Bonta? Never. I don\'t know what you mean by a bribe, Brakmarian. Get out of this tavern before things get really ugly.";
D.q[2368] = "What? Are we leaving now? But you didn\'t kill the rat! Are you out of your mind?";
D.q[6830] = "Who told you that I was talking to Srams? I guess it was Ares Truer. The poor loser didn\'t appreciate it when I beat him ten times in a row at ten different card games.\nYes, I sometimes play with Srams. Their minds and devious tactics lend themselves well to many games where chance isn\'t everything. I also play \"Funny Bones\" with them, but they don\'t appreciate the joke. However, my relationship with them is limited to the game, I don\'t spend time discussing my business with them, not like Ares Truer.";
D.q[5736] = "What are you doing here? Shouldn\'t you be guarding the Statuette of Sumens?";
D.q[3976] = "What? Kill a Wabbit plince at his ledding? That\'s vely dangelous!";
D.q[7010] = "What? You don\'t know who Greu Nouille is? Pfft, you noob.\nGreu Nouille is a Feca, and the greatest soul hunter of all time. Well, that said, she didn\'t do it all on her own, she had many adventurers supporting her, but I don\'t really want to talk about them. Anyway, one of these days I\'ll hop on over to see Greu Nouille. Yep, hop on over. Hop, Greu Nouille, Grenouille, Frog, do you get the joke? Pfft, kids these days...";
D.q[3077] = "What? He dares try to corrupt an officer under the oath of King Allister in the execution of her duties? Go back and tell him even if I could be bribed, it would take more than this bundle of change to do the job.";
D.q[6805] = "Nothing, nothing can happen to me while I don\'t say anything. I am not strong enough to protect myself on my own if I speak, and the leader of the militia won\'t send any of his men to monitor my enclosure night and day.";
D.q[1225] = "What? No, I don\'t like it. Move away from the wall. Now!";
D.q[5136] = "What? The Order of the Sugary Pancake? Don\'t you think it\'s a bit idiotic for a demon who can\'t eat anything... idiot.\nAll the same it sounds good... and I do like food myself... ok, that\'s it... I declare the Order of the Sugary Pancake OPEN!! The chief of the order will be the oh-so-powerful As\'Ruoy\'Dnim.";
D.q[1877] = "What? Marp? It can\'t be. She wouldn\'t pull that joke on me... hum?... Marp? MAAAARP?";
D.q[6898] = "It would be in Roy Sigfred\'s best interests to hurry because the trial will begin soon. Gnirreh\'s confession is crucial because without it Kit Dingaround\'s future is severely compromised.\nYou can tell Amayiro that we are on track but we are short of time. Perhaps he could delay the start of the trial a little.";
D.q[5474] = "What? Who are you? What are you making here? But wait... you\'re... you\'re from Bonta. And you know I was here. I suppose you want to arrest me? Pfff, idiot, fools... you have no idea how powerful I am. I\'m looking forward to watching you die!";
D.q[6952] = "Very wellssshhh... I\'ll takessshhh you to Vil Smissshe, but on ssshhhheveral conditionssshhh: we\'re gettingsssshhhh very boredssshhh heresssshh... Ssshhho you musssshhht convincssshhhhe a Bagrutte\'ssshhhh Inn waitresshhhhh to pay usssshhhh a visssshhhit... and you mussssshhht alsssshhho convincssshhhe Robin Gaywould, he breedsssshhhh Plain Boarssshhhhh... to give usssshhh one of hissshhh beassshhhtssshhh...";
D.q[2971] = "What? You dare bringing a Dofawa to me? This is not a Dofus, but a copy created from a Dragoturkey egg! Bringing such eggs in Astrub is liable to prison!";
D.q[6791] = "Kit Dingaround? The militiaman? Uh, well ... yes I remember something on the day of his arrest. He passed by here. No, actually he even came here, but not for me. He met with a stranger near my paddock and I overheard a few snippets of conversation. Not much, just a reference to Brakmar and something about confidential documents. That\'s about all.";
D.q[4919] = "You\'re looking for a Feca doll to comfort a spirit? That\'s very nice of you. I\'m more than happy to make one for you but you\'ll need to fetch the ingredients. Go get me 30 Flax Fibres for its clothes, 10 Lousy Pig Leathers for wings, 2 White Dreggon Shells for the eyes, 1 Rat Fang for the horns, 30 Boowolf Hair for the hair, 2 Farle\'s Pig Skins for the tongue, 10 Purple Bwork Leathers for the skin, 5 Plain Boar Leathers for the strap, 4 Prespic Paws for the feet, 3 Furious Trool Wool for stuffing and 30 Flax String to sew it all together.";
D.q[6798] = "You\'re not going to cut my throat in my sleep, are you? Or poison my wild boars\' water? I\'ve told you everything I know, don\'t harm me.";
D.q[6914] = "You\'re kidding I hope. No? If I sacrifice you for some unmentionable means, your body will rot until it smells worse than a tonne of rotten Snapper. You still want to volunteer for the sacrifice?";
D.q[6833] = "A foul-smelling Sram? Why didn\'t you say so before? If I answer will you stop boring me with your stories of owls and spelling? Okay.\nIt doesn\'t exactly smells like roses here, but I know a Sram who smells worse than a legion of Grossewer Rats. That must be why they let him come and go down the drain as he sees fit, they must think he\'s one of them.\nUsually he descends into the sewers through the entrance to the southeast of the city. His name? Gnirreh. It makes me think of rotten fish.\nNow that you\'ve got what you wanted go back to your boss and leave my wife out of it.";
D.q[6967] = "You Bontarians are a right bunch of hypocrites. You spit on us at every opportunity but when you need us, you get all sugary. And anyway, what makes you think that we, the Rogues, are in contact with the Demons of the Hours? You heard a silly rumour and you believed it?\nAnyway, I may, I repeat, I may be able to get what you need, but you\'ll have to do me a favour in return.";
D.q[6942] = "You went to so much trouble to find me? I am grateful, even though you probably aren\'t acting purely out of altruism. How can I express my gratitude?";
D.q[2174] = "What?! You ain\'t gone to see Howard? What the hell you waiting on, a shovel up the...";
D.q[1563] = "Whatever you do don\'t tell Amayiro I\'m here!";
D.q[4914] = "You don\'t look so good. Did you lose to an Ecaflip as well? Cursed are they, them and their indecent luck.";
D.q[3763] = "When I find enough junk to fill my bags, I\'ll go down to Astrub and fill my pockets!";
D.q[5079] = "When I heard the cook leave the Rasputin Cake for Amayiro, a sudden hunger came over me... so I went down to ask him for a snack. But when I was in the kitchen I heard voices above me. I can\'t understand it... there was a guard on duty and I didn\'t see anyone else come down.";
D.q[253] = "When I meet a really worthy adversary, I sometimes challenge them to a friendly fight.";
D.q[6073] = "When I see what the World of Twelve is becoming, I find that hiding my anger is the only wise thing to do.";
D.q[2586] = "Your path has been long, disciple, but at least you\'re on the right one, the one leading to the evil forest... But before you even think of going there, you should go talk to our Dopple tamer. Try and improve your fighting techniques on those creatures! You\'ll be glad of the practice once you reach your destination. Some say this forest has been forgotten by the gods... If you can\'t beat a dopple, I forbid you to set foot on this cursed land... It would be plain suicide!";
D.q[3411] = "When your realised destiny covers you like the soft coat of bear-fur, all the sacrifices you\'ve made won\'t seem that bad.";
D.q[4176] = "Where are the two Dragoturkey certificates I asked for?";
D.q[2531] = "Our Grandapan - Glory be to Grandapan! - has been a little... illuminated lately, he hasn\'t had his feet on the ground ever since he took an astral trip to meet the goddess. In short, he seems to have lost his mind... And his advisers are taking full advantage of it!";
D.q[6275] = "Shake on it. As of now we\'re going to start kidnapping Dragoturkeys. There\'s a cousin of mine who\'s looking.";
D.q[7520] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[7522] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[7524] = "Which Doploons do you want to exchange?";
D.q[7511] = "Which characteristic should this scroll modify?";
D.q[5913] = "Which milician came from the ranks of those dirtbags? Off the top of my head I\'d guess it was Tink Berval. That lazy sod is probably hanging round the Zaap as usual...";
D.q[2398] = "Which market building are you looking for?";
D.q[3269] = "Which profession do you want to learn?";
D.q[7512] = "Which characteristic should this scroll modify?";
D.q[7513] = "Which characteristic should this scroll modify?";
D.q[7514] = "Which characteristic should this scroll modify?";
D.q[3910] = "You\'re right on time! The King\'s looking for someone who can cut a figure in noble society. It\'s an important mission but I know you\'ll serve your King and do your best.";
D.q[200] = "There\'s no honour in conning unlucky people. Ecaflips only bet with other Ecaflips.";
D.q[5784] = "Who dares stray within the kingdom of the Guenelous bénis? Who dares molest the sleep of Al Beric, fallen king of the Guenelous bénis, possessor of the Tarn Helminth and guardian of Efiye Durin\'s treasure?";
D.q[5642] = "Who do you find prettiest? Sramettes, Sadidettes, Craettes, Bworkettes or peanuts?";
D.q[6345] = "Who do you think you\'re? Get out of my sight, or I\'ll whip you limb from limb...";
D.q[3165] = "Who\'s talking to me? \nCome closer, I can\'t see you!";
D.q[5692] = "Who exactly are you trying to frighten? Or are you just trying to impress your friends? Stop showing off for a while and make yourself useful... get me some clean clothes.";
D.q[6571] = "Who goes there? Show yourself!\nAh, it\'s you. What do you want?";
D.q[1671] = "Who lives by the sword? YOU DO? Well, you\'ll die by it. Didn\'t you know? If you want some gunpowder I\'m your man, just watch your fingers!";
D.q[6078] = "Who\'s crazy enough to come this way? Little pest, are you here to admire Djaul\'s power?";
D.q[2107] = "So, the next day, I went to my grandfather\'s former house, I went to his attic and all I found was a Goh set in the middle of the room. When I touched the board, a flame shot out of it, it\'s the only thing I can remember before I fainted, and when I woke up thirteen days later in the middle of the street, my grandfather\'s house had been sold by my parents. Ever since that day, the new owners have refused to let me in again, so I\'m hanging about in the tavern in search of allies, hoping to find this great spell...";
D.q[5350] = "Why are you back to see me? Did Raaga ask you?";
D.q[5641] = "Why did your soul decide to come back as a woman? How do you know that it wasn\'t in a man\'s body until now?";
D.q[1108] = "Why are you staring at me like that? Do you think that you can pick on me just cos I\'m smaller than you?";
D.q[2648] = "Why does my daughter have such a bullish personality? I\'ll never get her to marry anyone!";
D.q[5643] = "Why did your soul decide to come back as a man? How do you know that it wasn\'t in a woman\'s body until now, so nobody would get suspicious?";
D.q[1075] = "Why should I talk to you? Can\'t you see I\'m working?";
D.q[1948] = "Will you help me? Really? That\'s good of you. My beer deliveries arrive Amakna by the South road, I know that there\'s one leaving everyday but they never manage to get here. Walk along the South road, and you should meet a delivery man. Escort the delivery up to here.";
D.q[3005] = "With these scrolls you\'ll quickly be able to complete your training. I exchange them against 100 and 105 Gobball horns depending on their types. There are many persons that will exchange you scrolls in our world... You just have to find them!";
D.q[1986] = "Without this essence we cannot make any progress, make an effort...";
D.q[1420] = "What can I do for you, Brakmarian?";
D.q[5594] = "Some Brakmarians have burnt the town\'s food warehouses so the Bontarians have asked Merlinmagus Ambrosius to create a spell that will help the cereals grow quicker. I\'m not too worried myself because Merlinmagus is an incompetent imbecile, but if you want to be certain, you can go see for yourself. He works in the alchemists\' workshop.";
D.q[6743] = "If a Brakmarian tries to escape, he\'ll end up in prison.";
D.q[2313] = "Woo! That\'s more like it! But, we\'re not there yet! I\'m going to raise the stakes a little higher, young adventurer...";
D.q[3016] = "Wooohhoooo! Fallen warriors from the Crimson Dawn Battle, let your spirits talk to me! What is disturbing your sleep? Just tell me! Mmm?";
D.q[2944] = "Woof woof, wooo Wooffhooof....";
D.q[6712] = "I hope you having come to see me with your hands empty. I need some Scalding Poison and Magic Greenish Dye and I need it yesterday!";
D.q[3604] = "Work is good for your health ... though doing nothing would be best. Being forced is the essence of work.";
D.q[6558] = "Work for the army? Never again! I left a few years back, and I\'m not about to return now. I set up shop in Amakna so as to have some peace and quiet. There\'s no trouble here, and no worries. You should do the same before it\'s too late. What\'s more, if you\'re thinking of taking my advice, Amakna militia just recruited a young Iop who would be happy to help you get out of Bonta militia. If you continue on the path you\'re walking now, I can\'t do a thing for you, although maybe Otho Laringo will agree to help you. He owns the workshop in the North of the village.";
D.q[2062] = "Ya want to give us a hand? Haha, I like you Sacriers, always first to go underground, right? Well, your type\'s always welcome \'round here... Be careful though, one of our guys disappeared a few days ago, ain\'t no one seen a sniff a\' him. Somethin\'s going on down there. I don\'t like it. They even stopped us diggin\'... oh, well I\'ve said too much already. Look, I\'ll holler when I need ya!";
D.q[5565] = "It\'s too late, the spell has been cast! Now we can stuff ourselves till we burst without getting sick! As news goes, that\'s pretty good!";
D.q[1754] = "Xelors can use any weapon, but they handle hammers and sticks best.";
D.q[2399] = "Mining is my life... ahhh, the sharp sound of an eager pick, the cat\'s-eye glint of the hidden jewel... I\'ll never grow old as long as I live, my child... what a life!";
D.q[851] = "I\'ve just been told that during the assault, an apprentice warrior tried to skirt round enemies to take them by the rear... Of course, that moron has been captured. It wouldn\'t be a problem if that rookie wasn\'t well-informed about our next attack on Bonta. Recapture the sod before they question him. Yes, you heard me. Take other warriors with you and raid the enemy militia. The prison is located in the basement.";
D.q[1450] = "YOU\'VE GOT A NERVE! HE RAN OFF CRYING! You\'ll have a taste of my anger!";
D.q[2271] = "Yeah, Hellooo you! Stop staring at me, your eyes are like saucers. Yeah, I think you\'re needing a chat with an old mercenary like me.";
D.q[748] = "The cook was very satisfied with your work last time. He\'s got another peculiar dish to prepare today and I think he needs your help.";
D.q[3391] = "Yes! Good. Not over yet... nothing\'s over, nothing\'s ever finished. Fight again. And again. The key to your next fight.";
D.q[3980] = "Yes it\'s possible! If you manage to get in, I\'ll liven up the palty.";
D.q[3392] = "Yes! Good. Not over yet... nothing\'s over, nothing\'s ever finished. Fight again. And again. The key to your next fight.";
D.q[4099] = "I found a new master, I\'m going to meet him now.";
D.q[7115] = "Yes, I received a few potions from Otomai, the master alchemist. What would you like to exchange this potion for?";
D.q[3264] = "Yes, I used to be a school teacher.\nSome habits just won\'t change. \nDo you know where my son is?";
D.q[2746] = "Yes, a wumow. The Wa admitted he had the Dofus of a Dwagonesque Cawwot: the Cawwot Dofus. I said wumow because no one could weally confiwm ow denied the statement. And some adventuwews came back fwom theiw intewview with the Wa saying they had seen a magic egg. It somehow made the wumow more famous... Howevew, you should nevew be too suwe of youwself. This is the mowale of my stowy.";
D.q[1501] = "Yes, it\'s possible. Bring me 16 gold nuggets and a chafer\'s skull and I\'ll do it... plus 200 Kamas, of course.";
D.q[3093] = "Yes, some nice warm beer.";
D.q[3648] = "Yes, yes, I know... I\'ll continue if you really want me to. So anyway, after all this, I finally made it to the grocery... Negotiations were quite intense, I can tell you... I remember paying four Kamas for a week-old turnip... \'Well,\' I said to the shopkeeper, \'that\'s a turnip for the books\' hahaha!!!";
D.q[2407] = "Yes, what do you want?";
D.q[3424] = "Yes. That should do the trick. Go tell my friend, please.";
D.q[3887] = "Yessshh, you wissshh to talk to Vil Ssshhmisshhe. Alrightsshh. Follow me, ssshh.";
D.q[1077] = "Yes?";
D.q[1385] = "Yik cinik nik find iklik tik inswirs inik ir dictinirik. Jiksitik tiknik ibik hiwik yik wild fid ink skiril...";
D.q[3466] = "You afraid lil\' trool? You no real champion?";
D.q[816] = "Now he has new teeth, Mak wants to take his revenge, he\'s still as stubborn as ever... Anyway, with his choppers and brand new equipment, he intends to thrash you! Accept the challenge, I want to assess your progress since your last fight.";
D.q[2710] = "Yoohoohoo Pandawa, bless my shields, pliiiiiiiizz! Huh? Oh, I didn\'t see you! Can I help you?";
D.q[3035] = "Yooohhoooo! Yoooohooooo! Is there a spirit available to keep me company? Yooooohhhooooo! Anybody there? Yooooohhooooo! Yooohhoooo!";
D.q[48] = "You already know that profession, I\'ve got nothing more to teach you.";
D.q[5672] = "You again? I can see you don\'t give up easily. But if you think that\'s all you need to catch us, you\'re way wrong.";
D.q[5026] = "You again? If you\'ve come to kidnap me like the last time, I won\'t just call the guard!";
D.q[5096] = "You again?";
D.q[4482] = "You again? You came to kill me, I know it!\nWell I\'ll show you... this Whitish Fang might be beaten, but he\'s still got a few good teeth left!!";
D.q[4309] = "You again? The answer is no, now stop bothering me.";
D.q[1620] = "I love travelling. That\'s why I decided to offer a free trip to all my friends and villagers. Just pick a destination and you\'re there!";
D.q[1549] = "You always hang about the forests and fields instead of going to Bonta. Get going and everything else will fall into place.";
D.q[1602] = "You already have one of the 3 items i ask to you. It\'s a good start. You have to equip one necklace, one headband and one belt. You can drop them on the mobs near.";
D.q[3109] = "My old hideout? It\'s north west of Breeder Mountain, near the enchanted lakes. It\'s a beautiful, romantic area... just perfect to sit with your beloved and whisper sweet nothings to each other. I\'ll leave my hideout to whoever wants to live there. Personally I prefer the walls of my cell. Maybe Monabella could come live with me instead of going in this mosquito-infested pit! Hehehe...";
D.q[2554] = "Do you really want your head to flavour a barrel of Pandneken? You don\'t have a choice anyway...";
D.q[7618] = "What happened then? Well, some brave adventurers (and a lot of idiots too) stood against the two monsters without success. \nIt wasn\'t until the 24 Novamaire 639, that a group of warriors, summoned by Shika Ingalsse herself, managed to defeat the dragons for the first time. \nGrozilla and Grasmera did not go down easily, however, and so adventurers from all walks of life came to the warriors\' aid. \nOnce the dragons\' real motivation was known, the warriors of Shika were followed by the worshipers of the dark Demon Lord Rushu, who in turn were followed by the disciples of Rykke-Errel and the servants of Djaul. Not wanting to be outdone, the servants of the Sage Jiva also defeated the formidable creatures. \nWeakened by the many battles, Grozilla and Grasmera had no choice but to return to the Sanctuary after being repeatedly defeated by the servants of the other patrons of the months and various dignitaries.";
D.q[3468] = "You brave?";
D.q[1593] = "You bight albight... It bight eben take two of ub to bive you a bood hibing...";
D.q[7625] = "Either you don\'t have the courage to continue, or your friends have abandoned you. I can get you out of here if you wish.";
D.q[6205] = "I\'m sorry but you don\'t have the required status to access a bank safe. \n \n(Access to bank safes is restricted to players whose level is greater than 10)";
D.q[5985] = "You can at the right time. If you\'d been any later I would have given the mission to someone else.";
D.q[3572] = "You bring me back some wool and I can see a victory. Wool is victory, you get it? And yet, you give me the wool and the victory\'s yours. That\'s why wool is victory though it doesn\'t contain victory as you\'ll be keeping the victory, and this even if you give me the wool, you understand? Go and see Shaa Kwira, she\'ll help you to become more powerful.";
D.q[6452] = "You can ask a question so long as it\'s not completely idiotic. If it\'s dumb, you\'ll feel the lash of my whip.";
D.q[3450] = "You brought back my book. How nice of you!";
D.q[7623] = "By \'eck, \'appen as I\'m reet proud of yer, I am!";
D.q[5586] = "You can find the soul in question in Brakmar prison. As for your research, I think you would do well to start in the library.";
D.q[7589] = "My old friend will allow lucky premium access holders to face unique creatures that he has collected on his many travels around the World of Twelve. These creatures can be tackled alone or in groups, and my friend will reward all of the brave, victorious warriors.\nSo, come back on the 2nd of Descendre to discover the inside of this building and meet my friend.";
D.q[7624] = "Look at you, all upset because you\'re stuck here. I\'ll take you to the exit unless you\'re expecting a friend to show up.";
D.q[1203] = "You can now join the Order of the Sharp Eye.\nAre you still sure of your choice ?";
D.q[3698] = "You can only be here for one reason... to forget something... So, tell me, what is it? A lost love? A trade? Something you can\'t even utter out loud? Well, if you want me to make the right potion, you\'ll have to tell me!";
D.q[447] = "By looking at you I know you weren\'t talking about training, so you can use scrolls for that. If you give me 100 Boar Tusks, I\'ll give you a Small Vitality Scroll, if you\'d like.";
D.q[3689] = "You can tell Qwizitor that everything\'s fine.";
D.q[601] = "You can\'t afford this wonderful trip. Save up some money and come back again.";
D.q[1305] = "You defeated me with dignity. Though I don\'t really like your boss, I\'ll pay this tax. Consider it a reward for your victory.";
D.q[3467] = "You crush Trool. You brave!";
D.q[3527] = "You cross Bwork village and you alive! You strong! You help Goblin.";
D.q[3626] = "You destroy Piwis.";
D.q[4316] = "You dare to remind me of the event? Do you want to end up like him? Drunk and dodgy?";
D.q[1625] = "You don\'t have enough money";
D.q[1359] = "You don\'t even have 10 Kamas, rogue!";
D.q[6714] = "You didn\'t know? He sent us a letter from the Scaraleaf Plain to say he was visiting the Golden Scarabugly. According to him, it\'s but a myth and he wants to prove to everyone that such a creature doesn\'t exist. \nI fear things have taken a turn for the worse. Go to the Scaraleaf Dungeon and try to free Deni Hoobe, if he\'s still alive that is.";
D.q[1483] = "You don\'t know a thing, do you? The golden larva is legendary. Invested with the power of a god and the whole caboodle! Anyway I won\'t tell you the full story, you\'ve got the library for that. Just bring this larva back to its parents. QUICK!";
D.q[338] = "You\'re not a Farmer, so you can\'t help me. Come back when you\'re a Farmer.";
D.q[5890] = "You don\'t look like a disciple of mine. What exactly do you want?";
D.q[4201] = "You excelled in defeating the Tynril and you even showed us that nature itself can make mistakes. The Tynril will obviously have to make up his mind and make his offspring evolve if he wants to get back the throne he once deserved.";
D.q[4241] = "You failed little Scaraleaf!";
D.q[1497] = "You finally look like something better than Gobball faeces. Very good. Don\'t get dirty! You don\'t have to wear it all the time, but it\'s absolutely essential for the official warrior ceremonies.";
D.q[3223] = "You finally reached the door of the Dragon Pig\'s Den! I hope you managed to get the key from the Porcos! Well, now I\'ll ask you to give me both keys if you want to get in. Give me the key to the Dragon Pig\'s Den as well as that of the Dragon Pig Dungeon.\nDon\'t be so surprised! Tourists are meant to be fooled, everybody knows that! I\'ll just let you wander alone in this den and I\'ll see you later when you get out.";
D.q[2616] = "You find it?";
D.q[3338] = "You have a great soul, and a great... well, I respect you very much, I want you to know that. Please return when you can. It\'s just I get so lonely, you know. Oh well, happy wandering, my good friend. We are... friends I hope.";
D.q[2252] = "You got nothing? What are you doing standing round here, then? Go get some beer at the Innkeeper\'s, will ya... oh man!";
D.q[5739] = "You have a talent for always disturbing me at exactly the wrong time. For your sake, I hope you have a good reason for bothering me.";
D.q[732] = "You have been in the militia long enough to specialise in something. If you\'re interested, talk to the Master of the orders.\nIf not, I\'ve a little favour to ask you, I need 20 Agility Rings. Then I\'ll try to put 2 of them on each finger to see if it\'s effective!";
D.q[6751] = "You have no business here. Get going while there\'s still time.";
D.q[4928] = "You have found the Spirit of Light! Give it to me, I will take care of the rest.";
D.q[1489] = "You have to complete the training you\'ve started first. Come back to see me when you\'ve made more progress in the other trade.";
D.q[6117] = "You have shown initiative here. In time, your actions will prove important to our Order. I believe you deserve a promotion to Master of illusions considering all you\'ve done.\nCongratulations!";
D.q[3556] = "You hit goblin, you bring skin to me.";
D.q[1949] = "You haven\'t done what I asked you yet? Are you kidding me? Go on, hurry up!";
D.q[1482] = "You idiot! Has no one ever told you that a bunch of Larvae is as dangerous as a Kolerat? A bunch like that could bring a whole city down, submerged in wriggling larvae. Anyway, you had the right reaction. They all look dead except the golden one which is following yo... A GOLDEN LARVA? Djaul\'s Blood! You really are jinxed!";
D.q[3624] = "You hurry, me food go hips straight.";
D.q[111] = "You don\'t have enough Kamas to buy a ticket. \nYou need at least 10 Kamas.";
D.q[1078] = "You knew about this?... Well it\'s true, I don\'t go to that grotty Inn anymore. Their cat piss tastes too much like beer, it\'s revolting.";
D.q[6207] = "You know darling, discretion is one of the most important parts of my job. I really can\'t tell you anything about all this, but I know some people who can.";
D.q[2246] = "You know everything now... May your destiny be your guide, young apprentice!";
D.q[6063] = "By my pipe, I\'m lost again! Silouate is waiting for me... and I have the drink on top of that! He\'ll think I started without him.";
D.q[3812] = "You know some spells now kid. Why don\'t you go pay a visit some of those powerful creatures lurking in the dungeons round here? ";
D.q[2278] = "You know, those stone arches you see all over the world!? When you see one, get close to it. It will remember you. Then, you\'ll be able to teleport yourself there from any other Zaap for a few Kamas.";
D.q[2161] = "You like to get everything full, don\'t you? Well, I\'ve got a little job for you. You have to blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab blablablab. Well, do you accept?";
D.q[3567] = "You know, when the flag is raised, the whole country stands behind it. Well, not behind it, I mean, it\'s too small but, well, behind it, understand? I need a flag like that, but not because I want to stand behind it. I\'m not a coward.";
D.q[3274] = "You made it at last! I was starting to take roots!\nCome on! Follow me!";
D.q[4506] = "You managed it!? You found a competent tactician? I\'d like to believe that Justfa was in seventh heaven. This tactician helped us apply our strategies and to communicate with our men better than ever.";
D.q[3498] = "You loudmouth!";
D.q[489] = "You managed to find the manual... I won\'t say thank you, but my heart is in it.";
D.q[4196] = "You managed to defeat Gourlo the Terrible but I don\'t think that this will be enough to make him abandon his ship, though it should enable me to get back my belongings little by little.";
D.q[5765] = "You may know a few tricks, but you have yet to earn a reputation for yourself. It will only cost you 1,000 Kamas to become neutral.\nAnd don\'t forget, you can join the weaker alignment for free!";
D.q[6757] = "You might have come here in through one door, but you\'ll go out through the window.";
D.q[6715] = "You must be wondering what I\'m doing here, no? No, I\'m not afraid of Scaraleaves, I came of my own will to meditate. I can leave when I want.";
D.q[3399] = "You must carry out your mission.";
D.q[3991] = "You must become stwongew befowe you can follow me!";
D.q[1017] = "You must get the EXACT number of teeth a human being has from Gobballs. When you\'re done, bring them to Ned Etsith. He lives in the south-west of the city.";
